resource.chars: “BAC” factory, named after its first owner, who in 1890 launched the construction of a factory to produce penholders and metal eyelets (for shoes, corsets or military equipment). In 1904, it took the definitive name of Manufacture française des œillets.Owes its rescue to an architectural singularity which earned it a listing in the supplementary inventory of Historic Monuments in 1996.
